      "title": "Prompt 1: Lovable Setup",
      "text": "Build my app from this existing GitHub repo, fully autonomously, end-to-end:\nhttps://github.com/fayamonkey/AgentHub-Template\n\nIt is a plain Vite + React \"AI Hub\" with exactly three features: a content Hub, an Ideas pipeline\n(Kanban), and a Wins tracker. Adopt this repo's code AS-IS and wire it up to run in Lovable +\nLovable Cloud.\n\n## WORK AUTONOMOUSLY — no questions, no options, no stopping\n- Make EVERY technical decision yourself. Do NOT present option menus, do NOT ask me \"how should\n  I proceed\", do NOT pause for confirmation, do NOT stop midway. Build it straight through to the end.\n- The ONLY input you may request from me is at the very end: the GitHub token field and the\n  repo-name field (steps 4–5). Nothing else, ever.\n- This new project may be scaffolded on a different stack (e.g. TanStack Start). If so: DISCARD that\n  scaffold completely and replace it with THIS repo's plain Vite + React setup (its vite.config,\n  index.html, main.jsx, package.json dependencies, router, and the entire src/ and supabase/\n  folders). Do this WITHOUT asking — it is the expected, correct action.\n\n## Hard rules\n- Use this repo's plain Vite + React app exactly as-is. Do NOT redesign, rebuild, or \"modernize\" it\n  onto another stack.\n- Do NOT skip the GitHub vault content read. It is the core mechanic.\n- Do NOT add features (no Avatar, no Transcripts, no extra spaces). Only Hub + Ideas + Wins.\n\n## How it already works (implemented in this repo)\n- Hub: markdown \"cards\" come from the connected GitHub repo's /content folder, read AT RUNTIME via\n  the Supabase Edge Function supabase/functions/get-cards. It reads the private repo server-side\n  using a GITHUB_VAULT_TOKEN secret and returns the cards. No token in the browser. The hub calls it\n  from src/lib/vault.js.\n- Ideas + Wins: live in Lovable Cloud (Supabase). Schema in supabase/migrations/ (tables ideas,\n  wins, changelog; moving an idea to \"done\" auto-creates a win).\n- Config: src/config.js is the only file the user edits (ownerName, githubRepo, vaultFolder: \"content\").\n\n## Do exactly this, in order, without stopping\n1. Activate Lovable Cloud (Supabase) for this project.\n2. Apply the migrations in supabase/migrations/ (ideas/wins/changelog + functions).\n3. Deploy the get-cards edge function.\n4. Surface a secret input field labeled \"GITHUB_VAULT_TOKEN\" so the user can paste their GitHub\n   fine-grained token (with Contents: Read on their vault repo). Save it as the secret GITHUB_VAULT_TOKEN.\n5. At the same time, surface a SECOND input field directly above or next to the token field, labeled\n   \"Your Hub repo (format: yourname/agent-hub-xxxx)\". This is the GitHub repo Lovable created for\n   this project after the user connected GitHub. Wait for the user to paste the repo name.\n6. Once the user has provided BOTH the token and the repo name, set githubRepo in src/config.js to\n   the repo name the user pasted, set vaultFolder to \"content\", then rebuild.\n7. Build and run.\n\n## Done when\n- App builds and runs, nav shows only Home + 💡 Ideas + 🏆 Wins.\n- Ideas board (drag-and-drop) and Wins tracker work via Lovable Cloud.\n- Hub is ready to show markdown cards once GITHUB_VAULT_TOKEN is set AND src/config.js points at the\n  user's vault repo (an empty hub before that is expected, not an error).\n\nProceed now, end-to-end, without asking me anything except the token and repo-name fields."
